metadata.name: Silent Lab #40
metadata.description:
Finally, we used their weakness to trap them. They are sensitive to sound.

* Microphone is safe, the access to Mic is only from p5.js code to generate art on your pc, and not capture, save or send any voices.

Click to connect your voice and reload art if not working (‚ÄúSome browsers has bug on mic‚Äù).

The alien react to your mouse and microphone. Don't make them angry with high volume.

We won the game At the end of the war and jailed many of them to get some researches. We do not know where they come from! Furthermore, we do not know why they are fighting! But we know that they killed many of Our friends. Here is parallax rendering laboratory (In the story*) and you can resume researches on your alien.

Attention : don't touch them without mouse!

metadata.name: Overlay #9
metadata.description:
Overlay is inspired by the double exposure of analog photography and the 4-Color Process screen printing technique, where images are superimposed, mixing their
colors to form new ones, shapes are also mixed, sometimes they look like mountains, sometimes waves.

The initial price at unlocking will be 12 xtz. every 5 minutes, it will be reduced by 3 xtz to the death price of 1 xtz.

metadata.name: Chaosplot #95
metadata.description:
Continued exploration of the algorithm from "Chaospill" with a symmetric two tone style that is plotter friendly. The result can be rotated to whatever orientation works best for your display purposes. The code is presented unminified with comments and will be open sourced soon.

Live Mode Controls

Click to regenerate with a different starting seed.
1 - Save a SVG, the result is sized for 11"x17" prints with each color on a separate layer
2 - Save a PNG of the output
3 - Switch paper size to 8.5"x11" letter or A1 for different size plots
4 - Toggle HD mode which increases resolution and disables noise for printing
